description: The molecule is a 1-O-acyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 20 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated. It has a role as a mouse metabolite. It derives from an all-trans-lignoceric acid.
The molecule is a 1H-tetrazolium salt that is the monohydrochloride salt of 5-(and-6)-carboxyfluorescein. It has a role as a fluorochrome. It contains a fluorescein(1+).

The molecule is a 3beta-hydroxy steroid carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3beta,7alpha-dihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oic acid, obtained by formal deprotonation of the hydroxy group. It has a role as a metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 7alpha-hydroxypregnenolone.

The molecule is a 3-oxo fatty acid ascaroside anion that is the conjugate base of oscaroside B, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3. It is a 3-hydroxy fatty acid monocarboxylicate anion and a long-chain fatty acid anion. It derives from a linoleic acid(1-) and a (9Z,12Z)-9,12-octadecadienoate(1-).

The molecule is a 1,2-diaminoalkane that is 1,4-diaminobutane in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by a chloro group. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a member of diamines and a chlorinated alkane. It derives from a hydride of a butane.

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl amino tetrasaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2,3,6-tri-O-acetyl-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetylglucosamine in which the acetamido group has been replaced by an amino group. It has a role as an epitope.

The molecule is a 2-deoxy-D-galactonic acid in which the hydroxy group at position 4 is replaced by a methyl group. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 2-deoxymannonic acid.

The molecule is a 2',3'-dideoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate in which the ribose moiety is substituted at position 2' by a 2,4-diamino-6-oxo-6,7-dihydro-5H-cyclohepta[1,2-b]furan-5-yl group. The molecule is a 2-hydroxy-1,4-naphthoquinone in which the hydroxy group is located at position 1. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a member of 1,5-naphthaquinones and a 1-hydroxynaphthalene. It derives from a hydronaphthalen-1-one.

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside cation arising from protonation of the two amino groups and deprotonation of one of the three hydroxy groups of (2S,3R,4R,5S,6R)-6-deoxystreptothricin; major species at pH 7.3. It is a conjugate acid of a (2R,3S,4S,5R,6S)-2,6-diamino-3,4,5-trideoxy-alpha-D-streptotriose.

The molecule is a 2,2-dimethylcyclopropanecarboxaldehyde in which the two methyl groups are located on the same side of the cyclopropane ring. It has a role as a metabolite. It derives from a hydride of a dodecahydronaphthalene.
The molecule is a 2-amino-4-hydroxy-5-methylthiophene-3-carboxylic acid. It has a role as a metabolite. It derives from a thiophene.

The molecule is a 3,4-dihydroxyflavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7 and 4' and a prenyl group at position 3'. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a 3,6-dihydroyflavonol, a member of 7-hydroxyisoflavones, a monomethylated flavone and a 4'-hydroxyflavanone. It derives from a flavone.

The molecule is a 15-HPETE(1-) that is the conjugate base of 15-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3. It has a role as a human xenobiotic metabolite. It is a hydroperoxy polyunsaturated fatty acid anion and a long-chain fatty acyl anion. It derives from a 15(HETE)(1-). It is an enantiomer of a (15R)-15-HPTE(2-).

The molecule is a 7-oxabicyclo[2.2.1]hepta-2,5-diene derivative that is 6a-hydroxy-7a-methoxy-6a,7a-dihydro-2H-furo[2,3-b]furan-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 7a is replaced by a methyl group. The molecule is a 1,2-ethanediol in which one of the hydrogens is substituted by a methyl group. It has a role as a metabolite. It derives from a hydride of a 2-methylpropan-1-ol.
The molecule is a 1:1 complex of equimolar amounts of iron(II) and 1,10-phenanthroline. It has a role as a chelating agent. It contains a iron(2+) and a 1-10-Phen.

The molecule is a 2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and hydroxy groups of (2S,3R)-3-hydroxysuccinic acid; major species at pH 7.3. It has a role as a human metabolite and a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite. It is a conjugate base of a (2R,3S)-succinic acid.

The molecule is a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate(2-) in which the phosphate at position 1 is specified to be at the anionic site; major species at pH 7.3. It is a conjugate base of a 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myoinositol).

The molecule is a 16-membered macrolide isolated from the culture broth of Saccharomyces cerevisiae. It has a role as an antineoplastic agent, an antifungal agent and a fungal metabolite. It is an acetate ester, an epoxide, a lactone, a macrocycle, a member of phenols, an organic heteropentacyclic compound and a secondary alcohol. It derives from a hydride of an ergostane.

The molecule is a 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3R,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z)-docosahexaenoic acid. The molecule is a 1H-pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidin-4(3H)-one that is substituted at positions 1, 2, 4, 5, 6 and 7 by chloro, methyl, hydroxy, amino, methyl and chloro groups, respectively. It has a role as an antineoplastic agent. It is a member of pyrazolopyrimidines, a primary amino compound, an organochlorine compound and an organic heterotetracyclic compound.

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is substituted by a beta-D-ribofuranosyl group. It has a role as a metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 3-beta-D-ribosyl-alpha-D-glucofuranose.
The molecule is a 3-amino-5-oxopentanoic acid. It has a role as a metabolite. It is a tautomer of a 3-oxo-Delta(1)-pyrroline-2-carboxylic acid.

The molecule is a 16-membered macrolide antibiotic that is 14,15-dideoxy-15-deoxytetracycline in which the 3-hydroxy group has been oxidised to the corresponding 3-keto group. It has a role as an antineoplastic agent and a microbiological assay reagent. It is a tetracyclic lactone, a 3-oxo monocarboxylic acid derivative and a 16-member ring compound. It derives from a hydride of a 12,13-didehydrotetracyclines.

The molecule is a 1,2-dichloro-4-nitrobenzene in which one of the chlorines is substituted by a hydroxy group. It has a role as an environmental contaminant. It is a member of monochlorobenzenes, a 1,3-dicholorobenzene, an organochlorine compound and a 2-hydroxybenzoic acid.
The molecule is a 3,4-dihydroxy-L-phenylalanine. It has a role as a metabolite. It is a tautomer of a L-DOPA zwitterion.

The molecule is a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl and oleoyl respectively. It has a role as a mouse metabolite. It derives from an oleic acid and a hexadecanoic acid.

The molecule is a 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate in which the hydroxy group at position 4 is replaced by a methyl group. It has a role as a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite and an Escherichia coli metabolite.

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 4 is substituted by a 2-deoxycytosyl group. It is a 3-deoxy-D-galactosamine derivative, a member of cytidines and a 1-deoxynucleoside. It derives from a cytidine.

The molecule is a 2-aminopentanoic acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 2-amino-5-oxopentanediolic acid; major species at pH 7.3. It is a tautomer of a 2-oxo-5-amino-pentanedioate.

The molecule is a 2-O-acyl-alpha-D-galactopyranosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucopyranose in which the acyl group is specified as heptadecanoyl. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a 3-beta-hydroxyacyl monocarboxylic acid and a 2-O-carboxy-3-O-hexadecanoxy-1,4-di-O-alkyl-alpha-D-Galp. It derives from a heptanoic acid.

The molecule is a 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is the 3',5'-cyclic phosphate of ribose 5-phosphate. It has a role as an Escherichia coli metabolite and a mouse metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 3'-5'cyclic ribonucleotidyl phosphate(3-).

The molecule is a 1H-pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidin-4(3H)-one that is 5-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)-2-(pyridin-2-yl)pyrazol-3-one substituted at position 1 by a 4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl group. It is a 3',4',5',7'-tetrahydroxyflavanone, a monosaccharide derivative, a member of flavonoids and a 2-deoxy-3-O-methyl-alpha-D-glucoside. It derives from a quercetin.
The molecule is a 1,4-cyclohexadiene in which the two double bonds are trans. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a conjugate base of a (2E,6E)-2,6-dimethyloct-2-en-1-ol.

The molecule is a 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 3-deoxy-D-arabino-heptulosonic acid 7-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3. It has a role as a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite and a human metabolite. It is a conjugate base of a (3R,4R,5S,6R)-3,4,5-trihydroxy-6-(phosphonooxy)hexanoic acid.

The molecule is a 6alpha-hydroxy steroid that is 5alpha-cholest-7-en-3beta-ol substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 17 and by an oxo group at position 3 (the 3beta,6alpha,17beta-stereoisomer). It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a 3-oxo-Delta(4) steroid, a 6alpha-steroid and a 17-oxosteroid. It derives from a hydride of a cholesterol.

The molecule is a 1,2,3,4-tetrahydropyrimidine that is 2,4-diaminopyrimidine in which one of the hydrogen atoms attached to the nitrogen at position 4 has been replaced by a methyl group. It is a member of 2-amino-4-methylpyrimidines and a pyrimidine derivative.

The molecule is a 7-oxoabietane diterpenoid that is abietane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7 and methyl groups at positions 2 and 3. It has a role as a plant metabolite.

The molecule is a 20-HETE(1-) that is the conjugate base of 20-hydroxyeicosatetraenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3. It is a 20(HETE)(1-) and a long-chain fatty acid anion. It derives from an arachidonate(1-). It is an enantiomer of a (20R)-HETE-(1-)".

The molecule is a 2-amino-3-hydroxybutanoic acid in which the hydroxy group is substituted at position 4. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a tautomer of a 4-hydroxypyrrolidine-2-carboxylic acid zwitterion.

The molecule is a 1,2-dihydroxybenzene in which the hydrogens at positions 3 and 5 are replaced by methyl groups. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 3,5-dimethylcatechol.

The molecule is a 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl). It derives from an octadecanoic acid. It is a conjugate acid of a 1-(stearoylamino)-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(1-).

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been substituted by a 2-acetamido-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residue. It is an amino disaccharide and a member of acetamides. It derives from a beta-D-GalpNAc(2->3)-D-Glc.

The molecule is a 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is 2-hydroxyglutaric acid in which one of the hydrogens at position 5 has been replaced by a sulfanyl group. It derives from a 2-amino-3-sulfanylpropanoic acid. It is a conjugate acid of a 5-(sulfinyl)sulfanylglutamate(1-).

The molecule is a 1,2-dihydroxybenzene that is 1,4-naphthoquinone in which one of the hydrogens at position 4 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 4-hydroxy-1,5-naphthyridine-2,7-dione.
The molecule is a 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-octadecyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine; major species at pH 7.3.

It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a member of pyrans, a monocarboxylic acid amide, an organic heterotricyclic compound, an aromatic ketone and a secondary alcohol. The molecule is a 3-oxo-Delta(5)-steroid that is 5alpha-cholestan-3-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 20. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a 7alpha-hydroxy steroid, a 20-oxosteroid and a 3-oxidosteroid. It derives from a hydride of a cholesterol.

The molecule is a 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is the 3',5'-cyclic phosphate of deoxyguanosine. It has a role as an Escherichia coli metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 3'-5' cyclic AMP(3-).

The molecule is a 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyisocaproic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3. It is a 2-amino-3-methylbutanoate 1-oxide and a 3-oxobutanoate. It derives from a hydroxyisobutyrate.

The molecule is a 1,4-dihydropyrimidin-2(1H)-one in which the hydrogen at position 5 is substituted by a methyl group. It has a role as a metabolite. It is a tautomer of a 5-methyl-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-4-one.

The molecule is a 12-membered amino oligosaccharide consisting of two alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residues, one alpha-D-mannopyranose residue and one beta-D-glucofuranose residue linked sequentially (1->4) and (2->6). It has a role as an epitope.

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been substituted by a 2,3-dideoxy-alpha-L-ribo-hex-2-enopyranosyl group. It is a member of 2-deoxypentoses, an amino monosaccharide and a 1,2-dideoxypentoside. It derives from a 3-deoxy-D-manno-2-octulosonic acid.
The molecule is a 2-deoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3, 4 and 6 have been replaced by beta-D-glucopyranosyl groups.

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside in which the anomeric hydrogen is replaced by a 3,4-dihydroxy-5-sulfophenyl group. It has a role as a bacterial metabolite. It is a conjugate acid of a 2-aminomethanesulfonate(1-).

The molecule is a 7-oxabicyclo[2.2.1]hepta-2,5-dien-2-one that is 6a,7a-dihydro-6a-methoxy-7a-methyl-6,6a-dimethyl-2H-furo[3,2-g]furo[2,3-b]furan-4-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6 and a methyl group at position 7. The molecule is a 1,3,4-thiadiazolidine-2-sulfonic acid in which the two hydrogen atoms of the sulfonic acid group are replaced by methyl groups. It has a role as a human metabolite. It contains a 1-methylthiadiazol-2-ium.

The molecule is a 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified are hexadecyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively. It has a role as a mouse metabolite. It derives from an octadecanoic acid.
The molecule is a 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl and acyl groups are specified as heptadecyl and palmitoyl respectively. It has a role as a mouse metabolite.

The molecule is a 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and hydroxy groups of 2-hydroxy-3,4-dihydroxycoumarin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

The molecule is a 1,3,4-thiadiazole-2,5-dione in which the 2-hydroxy group is substituted by a 2,4-dichlorophenyl group. It has a role as an antineoplastic agent. It is a member of thiazoles, an aromatic ether, an organochlorine compound and a 1,2,3-triazole. It derives from a 4-chlorobenzoyl chloride.

The molecule is a 2-oxo fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (2S,3R)-2-hydroxydecanoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It has a role as a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite. It is a monocarboxylic acid, an alpha-D-galactopyranosiduronic acid, a secondary alcohol and an ascarosylic acid.
The molecule is a 1,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodiazepin-2(3H)-one that is 1,2,3,4-tetrazole substituted at position 1 by a methyl group. It has a role as a metabolite.

The molecule is a 2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is substituted by a 2-deoxymannopyranosyl group. It is a member of alpha-D-mannosides and a 1,2-dideoxy-D-glycose derivative. It derives from an alpha-D-Manp(2->3)-D-Glc.

The molecule is a 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and oxo groups of 2-hydroxy-3-oxopropionic acid; major species at pH 7.3. It is a conjugate base of a 2-HOPA(2-).

The molecule is a 4-hydroxyphenylacetic acid in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 of the phenyl ring are substituted by methyl groups and the carboxy group is substituted by a 2,3-dihydro-1H-indol-1-yl group. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a member of indoles, a 4-hydroyphenyl acetic acid and a secondary carboxamide. It derives from a hydroxyindole-3-acetic acid.

It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a 2-amiropiolic acid derivative and a member of hydroxycarboxylic acids. It derives from a 3-hydroxybutyric acid.

The molecule is a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively. It is a conjugate base of a 1-oleoyl-2-(9Z-octadecenyloxy)-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate.

The molecule is a 1,2,3,4-tetrahydropyridine that is the N-oxide of 1-(2,6-dichlorophenyl)-3-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)-2,5-dihydro-1H-pyrazol-4-ium. It has a role as a metabolite. It is a member of pyrazolines and a N-oxides.
The molecule is a 3-methylcyclohexane that is 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8-octahydronaphthalene substituted by a methyl group at position 3. It has a role as a plant metabolite.
